Package: botornot
Title: Classify Twitter Users as Bot or Not
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Michael Wayne", "Kearney", , 
    "kearneymw@missouri.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"), 
    comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0730-4694"))
Description: Classify Twitter accounts as bot or not bot. The packagae uses 
    a gradient boosted model, which was trained using thousands of real 
    automated (bot) and non-automated Twitter accounts, and returns estimated
    probabilities of whether supplied accounts are bots.
URL: https://github.com/mkearney/botornot
BugReports: https://github.com/mkearney/botornot/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    gbm,
    rlang,
    rtweet,
    textfeatures,
    tibble
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    roxygen2,
    testthat
Remotes:
    mkearney/textfeatures
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: yes
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1.9000
